-- South Africa’s Thomas Aiken Wins Avantha Masters Golf by 3 Shots
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-03-17T15:06:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-17/south-africa-s-thomas-aiken-wins-avantha-masters-golf-by-3-shots.html
South Africa’s Thomas Aiken scored
a final-round 67, 5-under par, to win golf’s Avantha Masters in
Delhi by three shots today.  Aiken finished on 23-under, ahead of India’s Gaganjeet
Bhullar in second spot. Aiken picked up a prize of 300,000 euros
($392,000) in his second win on the European Tour.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 